"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5195627-2024-01-11-2024-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-seine\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympics PARIS - Tony Estanguet is one of the great French Olympians of all time, a canoeist who is the country's first athlete to have won gold at three different Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 34, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 55, \"end\": 61, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9899865188447372, \"rank\": 0.007057667900876954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 72, \"to\": 80}, {\"ngram\": \"a canoeist\", \"from\": 82, \"to\": 92}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's first athlete\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 127}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 144}, {\"ngram\": \"three different Games\", \"from\": 148, \"to\": 169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of the four Olympics in which he participated, the 2008 Games in Beijing was the only time Estanguet, who is now president of the Paris 2024 Olympic committee, did not win.\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 240, \"end\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9326922828559617, \"rank\": 0.07216497225262183, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0650135511055704e-26, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the four Olympics\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 195}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2008 Games\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 236}, {\"ngram\": \"the only time\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 275}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 297}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement A nice consolation, he served as French flag bearer for the opening ceremony that summer in 2008.\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A nice consolation\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet it is not the opening ceremony of the four in which he marched that he most fondly remembers.\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 559, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 496}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I remember very well all four, but for me, very strongly the first one, when I entered in Sydney in the Olympic Stadium for the opening ceremony for my first games,\\\" Estanguet said from the sprawling Paris Games headquarters in Saint-Denis.\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 652, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.999999701119622, \"rank\": 2.345166948142858e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999980607945576, \"rank\": 1.9391289207740993e-06, \"text\": \"Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Stadium\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 681}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 706}, {\"ngram\": \"my first games\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 737}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprawling Paris Games headquarters\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was two days before my competition, and then everything stops and you feel something very strong, to be a part of something unique,\\\" Estanguet said.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 956, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my competition\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 931}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So I know how important it is for the athletes.\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1004}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I know that it is also important for all the people involved, because it's the biggest TV audience of the Games.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the people\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest TV audience\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's more than 1 billion people watching the opening ceremony, so in one night, in three hours' time, you have to send a very strong message of what those games would be about.\\\"\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 1 billion people\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1150}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"one night\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1197}, {\"ngram\": \"three hours' time\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"a very strong message\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"those games\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1279}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Games, with Estanguet in charge, aim to send the strongest, most audacious opening statement in the history of the modern Olympics.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Paris Games\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1313}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"the strongest, most audacious opening statement\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers have devised a July 26 opening ceremony that is a floating parade along the Seine River - a 3.7-mile journey in which delegations from 200 countries will board 100 boats for a 45-minute ride that begins near the national library, winds past the Cathedral of Notre Dame (still under repair after a devastating fire in 2019) and the Louvre, passes by all of Paris' famous centrally located gardens, and ends at the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1783, \"end\": 1789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.7395776312405925, \"rank\": 0.3521231007521527, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.069115392284146e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"a July 26 opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"a floating parade\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine River\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"a 3.7-mile journey\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1560}, {\"ngram\": \"delegations\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"200 countries\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1600}, {\"ngram\": \"100 boats\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1621}, {\"ngram\": \"a 45-minute ride\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1642}, {\"ngram\": \"the national library\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"winds\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"the Cathedral\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre Dame\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"repair\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"a devastating fire\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1765}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Imagine, from a U.S. Olympic perspective, LeBron James, Simone Biles, Katie Ledecky, and Justin Thomas standing on the same boat, one foot on the rail, waiving to the north and south of the world-famous river as they approach a glittering Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 2132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1936, \"end\": 1948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 1950, \"end\": 1963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Thomas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.774608274574771e-27, \"text\": \"Justin Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Thomas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Imagine\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"a U.S. Olympic perspective\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 1920}, {\"ngram\": \"the same boat\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"the rail\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"the north\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2052}, {\"ngram\": \"south\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2062}, {\"ngram\": \"the world-famous river\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2088}, {\"ngram\": \"a glittering Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, 15,000 athletes are expected for the Paris Games, including numerous international basketball and golf stars (like, say,French sensation Victor Wembanyama, and Rory McIlroy), to say nothing of the stars of traditional Olympic sports like track and field.\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2263, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9899865188447372, \"rank\": 0.007057667900876954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2280, \"end\": 2297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"score\": 0.9999841253320871, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Wembanyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\"}, {\"begin\": 2303, \"end\": 2315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rory McIlroy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"15,000 athletes\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2158}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2191}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous international basketball and golf stars\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2332}, {\"ngram\": \"the stars\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2345}, {\"ngram\": \"traditional Olympic sports\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2375}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2386}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 2391, \"to\": 2396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No Summer Olympics has ever opened outside a stadium.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2416}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Spectators are expected to number in the hundreds of thousands and will view the parade from the banks of the river, either with a ticket they purchased or through a lottery of free tickets that has yet to take place.\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Advertisement Spectators\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"the hundreds\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2516}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2529}, {\"ngram\": \"the parade\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2554}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2582}, {\"ngram\": \"a ticket\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"a lottery\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"free tickets\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2656}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Estanguet and his chief deputies studied, considered, and dissected their own plan for 1.5 years before announcing it in 2021.\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2813, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2696}, {\"ngram\": \"his chief deputies\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2719}, {\"ngram\": \"their own plan\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2769}, {\"ngram\": \"1.5 years\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 2783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years later, with wars raging in Ukraine and the Middle East, and some nine years after the Paris terrorist attacks, the 2024 Games will open on the Seine River, organizers toldThe Athleticon Thursday.\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2853, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999956420596762, \"rank\": 4.251224496486677e-06, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris terrorist attacks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wars\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2842}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle East\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 2880}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Games\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 2951}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine River\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 2980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contingency plans, for security or other concerns, are related to the size of the crowds, and not a potential moving of the ceremony to a more traditional setting, like a stadium.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Contingency plans\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3040}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 3046, \"to\": 3054}, {\"ngram\": \"other concerns\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3072}, {\"ngram\": \"the size\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3097}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowds\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3111}, {\"ngram\": \"not a potential moving\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3139}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3155}, {\"ngram\": \"a more traditional setting\", \"from\": 3159, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have different plans, but all plans focus on having the ceremony on the river Seine,\\\" said Lambis Konstantinidis, director of planning and coordination for the Paris Games and a veteran of multiple Olympic organizing efforts.\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3433, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"different plans\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3228}, {\"ngram\": \"all plans\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3243}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3272}, {\"ngram\": \"the river Seine\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"Lambis Konstantinidis\", \"from\": 3299, \"to\": 3320}, {\"ngram\": \"director\", \"from\": 3322, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"planning\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3342}, {\"ngram\": \"coordination\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3359}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3379}, {\"ngram\": \"a veteran\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3393}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple Olympic organizing efforts\", \"from\": 3397, \"to\": 3432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For months in Paris, French security experts have raised doubts about securing the banks of the Seine, and in December French President Emmanuel Macron said there was \\\"obviously a Plan B, a Plan C\\\" in the face of elevated security risks.\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3449, \"end\": 3454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.069115392284146e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3456, \"end\": 3462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9899865188447372, \"rank\": 0.007057667900876954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3531, \"end\": 3536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.223268769217811e-18, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 3554, \"end\": 3570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 3571, \"end\": 3586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"months\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3445}, {\"ngram\": \"doubts\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3498}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3523}, {\"ngram\": \"December\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3553}, {\"ngram\": \"obviously a Plan B\", \"from\": 3603, \"to\": 3621}, {\"ngram\": \"a Plan C\", \"from\": 3623, \"to\": 3631}, {\"ngram\": \"the face\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3644}, {\"ngram\": \"elevated security risks\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For us to come out and make this sort of bold commitment, we had a significant reassurance from the authorities that (securing an on-river opening ceremony) was feasible,\\\" Konstantinidis said.\", \"from\": 3674, \"to\": 3867, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3681}, {\"ngram\": \"this sort\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3712}, {\"ngram\": \"bold commitment\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3731}, {\"ngram\": \"a significant reassurance\", \"from\": 3740, \"to\": 3765}, {\"ngram\": \"the authorities\", \"from\": 3771, \"to\": 3786}, {\"ngram\": \"river\", \"from\": 3808, \"to\": 3813}, {\"ngram\": \"Konstantinidis\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It requires means, it requires investment, but what the President said - we are already doing.\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3963, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"means\", \"from\": 3881, \"to\": 3886}, {\"ngram\": \"investment\", \"from\": 3900, \"to\": 3910}, {\"ngram\": \"the President\", \"from\": 3921, \"to\": 3934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have to have a contingency plan, but we need to have one anyway for a number of reasons that are not all security-related.\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 4089, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a contingency plan\", \"from\": 3980, \"to\": 3998}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 4035, \"to\": 4043}, {\"ngram\": \"reasons\", \"from\": 4047, \"to\": 4054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 It's not about having it at the river Seine or in the stadium or someone else, but, could it look different?\\\"\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 4201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the river Seine\", \"from\": 4120, \"to\": 4135}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadium\", \"from\": 4142, \"to\": 4153}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 4157, \"to\": 4164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Konstantinidis said organizers were still determining an attendance target, originally quoted at 600,000 spectators, that could be significantly reduced but still count in the hundreds of thousands.\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Konstantinidis\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4217}, {\"ngram\": \"organizers\", \"from\": 4223, \"to\": 4233}, {\"ngram\": \"an attendance target\", \"from\": 4257, \"to\": 4277}, {\"ngram\": \"600,000 spectators\", \"from\": 4300, \"to\": 4318}, {\"ngram\": \"the hundreds\", \"from\": 4375, \"to\": 4387}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Paris organizers say there will be roughly 2,000 private security guards in the seating venues closest to the river and about 45,000 security forces on the outer perimeter - 15 times the number of Paris police normally deployed for the entire Paris historical district.\", \"from\": 4403, \"to\": 4687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4418, \"end\": 4423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.069115392284146e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4615, \"end\": 4620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.069115392284146e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4661, \"end\": 4666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.069115392284146e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"typ